<article class="prose dark:prose-invert">
  <h2>Designing for Testability</h2>
  <p>Early on, the template favored visual polish over testability. Introducing predictable DOM structure (IDs/roles) and stable focus order made E2E coverage straightforward.</p>

  <h3>Takeaways</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Prefer role-based locators where possible.</li>
    <li>Keep interactive controls from overlapping at mobile widths.</li>
    <li>Make the main region focusable for skip links.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Case-insensitive Tags</h2>
  <p>Two inputs like <em>IndieWeb</em> and <em>indieweb</em> can conflict when slugs collide. A case-insensitive dedupe in the <code>tagList</code> collection prevents output conflicts.</p>
</article>
